Submitted By:            Combined: Douglas R. Reno (build fix) + still image + tune fix + TD OBU fix + clap fix
Date:                    2026-03-21
Initial Package Version: 1.21.2
Upstream Status:         Pending
Origin:                  Upstream (PR #1680) + fixes
Description:             Fixes building libheif with SVT-AV1 4.0 and later.
                         Four changes on top of the original build fix:

                         1. Still image mode (SVT-AV1 >= 4.0.0):
                            avif=true, intra_period_length=-1, fps=1/1.

                         2. tune=SSIM fallback to PSNR (SVT-AV1 >= 4.0.0):
                            SVT-AV1 4.x requires CRF for tune=SSIM but libheif uses
                            CQP. Fall back silently to PSNR.

                         3. Strip Temporal Delimiter OBU from output bitstream:
                            AVIF spec (ISO 23000-22 §2.1) forbids TD OBUs in image
                            items. SVT-AV1 in avif mode prepends one (2 bytes).
                            Firefox rejects such files. Strip after encode.

                         4. Fix clap box fractional offset (box.cc):
                            SVT-AV1 rounds odd dimensions up (461→462) for YUV420.
                            libheif adds a clap box with offset=-(1/2) pixel which
                            is non-integer — Firefox rejects per AVIF spec.
                            Fix: expand clap visible area by 1px when diff is odd,
                            making the offset 0 (integer). One pixel of padding
                            becomes visible but this is imperceptible.

